comments.author: BlackHatCoiner
comments.body: Quote from: Anas35 on November 23, 2024, 02:23:24 PMFrom my Dat file I have my old backup where the wif is present but in asciiThe WIF means "Wallet Import Format", and no wallet software imports it in the format you've presented. This is the correct format: https://learnmeabitcoin.com/technical/keys/private-key/wif/.Did you perhaps bought this wallet instead? Don't be too shy to admit it, a lot of people in here come often, asking for helping them to recover "their" bitcoin, when in reality, it's just a fake wallet file they bought from a scammer, with nothing in it.

Be very careful on what actual data you are posting; no admin can help you if your private key ends up in wrong hands and quite small chance even police would help. Better watch your back.3. Maybe will get you to some private messages "willing to help" and actually trying to steal your coins, but nothing else. Get more constructive.
